attributes.name: UNC1069
attributes.description: UNC1069 is a suspected North Korean financial crime group, which may be related to APT38 with low confidence. UNC1069 has targeted a variety of financial services firms and cryptocurrency exchanges. UNC1069 commonly uses spearphishing that leads to a LONEJOGGER shortcut file, which can lead to UNC1069's non-public implants such as LONERUNNER, WHITEHAUL, or POWERHOUSE. UNC1069 has been active since at least 2018.

value.description: Detects execition of commands and binaries from the context of The program compatibility assistant (Pcalua.exe). This can be used as a LOLBIN in order to bypass application whitelisting.

value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects a suspicious curl process start on Windows with set useragent options

value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton
value.description: Detects potentially suspicious child processes spawned by PowerShell

value.title: MacOS Scripting Interpreter AppleScript
value.author: Alejandro Ortuno, oscd.community
value.description: Detects execution of AppleScript of the macOS scripting language AppleScript.

value.title: Suspicious Curl.EXE Download
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a suspicious curl process start on Windows and outputs the requested document to a local file

value.title: Suspicious Curl Change User Agents - Linux
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a suspicious curl process start on linux with set useragent options

value.title: DeviceCredentialDeployment Execution
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects the execution of DeviceCredentialDeployment to hide a process from view

value.title: Suspicious Curl File Upload - Linux
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), Cedric MAURUGEON (Update)
value.description: Detects a suspicious curl process start the adds a file to a web request

value.title: Suspicious Msiexec Quiet Install From Remote Location
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects usage of Msiexec.exe to install packages hosted remotely quietly

value.title: Curl Download And Execute Combination
value.author: Sreeman, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Adversaries can use curl to download payloads remotely and execute them. Curl is included by default in Windows 10 build 17063 and later.

value.title: MSHTA Suspicious Execution 01
value.author: Diego Perez (@darkquassar), Markus Neis, Swisscom (Improve Rule)
value.description: Detection for mshta.exe suspicious execution patterns sometimes involving file polyglotism

value.title: Msiexec Quiet Installation
value.author: frack113
value.description:
Adversaries may abuse msiexec.exe to proxy execution of malicious payloads.
Msiexec.exe is the command-line utility for the Windows Installer and is thus commonly associated with executing installation packages (.msi)

value.title: Windows Shell/Scripting Application File Write to Suspicious Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects Windows shells and scripting applications that write files to suspicious folders

value.title: Msiexec.EXE Initiated Network Connection Over HTTP
value.author: frack113
value.description:
Detects an initiated network connection by "Msiexec.exe" over port 80 or 443.
Adversaries might abuse "msiexec.exe" to install and execute remotely hosted packages.

value.title: Suspicious Microsoft OneNote Child Process
value.author: Tim Rauch (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), Elastic (idea)
value.description: Detects suspicious child processes of the Microsoft OneNote application. This may indicate an attempt to execute malicious embedded objects from a .one file.

value.title: Launch Agent/Daemon Execution Via Launchctl
value.author: Pratinav Chandra
value.description: Detects the execution of programs as Launch Agents or Launch Daemons using launchctl on macOS.

value.title: Suspicious LNK Double Extension File Created
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), frack113
value.description: Detects the creation of files with an "LNK" as a second extension. This is sometimes used by malware as a method to abuse the fact that Windows hides the "LNK" extension by default.

value.title: Potential Goopdate.DLL Sideloading
value.author: X__Junior (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects potential DLL sideloading of "goopdate.dll", a DLL used by googleupdate.exe

value.title: Suspicious MSHTA Child Process
value.author: Michael Haag
value.description: Detects a suspicious process spawning from an "mshta.exe" process, which could be indicative of a malicious HTA script execution

value.title: Local Network Connection Initiated By Script Interpreter
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects a script interpreter (Wscript/Cscript) initiating a local network connection to download or execute a script hosted on a shared folder.

value.title: Potentially Suspicious Malware Callback Communication
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects programs that connect to known malware callback ports based on statistical analysis from two different sandbox system databases

value.title: Startup Item File Created - MacOS
value.author: Alejandro Ortuno, oscd.community
value.description:
Detects the creation of a startup item plist file, that automatically get executed at boot initialization to establish persistence.
Adversaries may use startup items automatically executed at boot initialization to establish persistence.
Startup items execute during the final phase of the boot process and contain shell scripts or other executable files along with configuration information used by the system to determine the execution order for all startup items.

value.title: Suspicious PowerShell Get Current User
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the use of PowerShell to identify the current logged user.

value.title: Suspicious Process Discovery With Get-Process
value.author: frack113
value.description: Get the processes that are running on the local computer.

value.title: Outbound Network Connection Initiated By Script Interpreter
value.author: frack113, Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a script interpreter wscript/cscript opening a network connection to a non-local network. Adversaries may use script to download malicious payloads.

value.title: Potential PowerShell Obfuscation Using Alias Cmdlets
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects Set-Alias or New-Alias cmdlet usage. Which can be use as a mean to obfuscate PowerShell scripts

value.title: Creation of an Executable by an Executable
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the creation of an executable by another executable

value.title: Python Initiated Connection
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects a Python process initiating a network connection. While this often relates to package installation, it can also indicate a potential malicious script communicating with a C&C server.

value.title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets
value.author: James Pemberton / @4A616D6573, Endgame, JHasenbusch, oscd.community, Austin Songer @austinsonger
value.description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via CommandLine

value.title: Password Protected Compressed File Extraction Via 7Zip
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects usage of 7zip utilities (7z.exe, 7za.exe and 7zr.exe) to extract password protected zip files.

value.title: Suspicious Script Execution From Temp Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Max Altgelt (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton
value.description: Detects a suspicious script executions from temporary folder

value.title: Suspicious Call by Ordinal
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects suspicious calls of DLLs in rundll32.dll exports by ordinal

value.title: Office Application Initiated Network Connection To Non-Local IP
value.author: Christopher Peacock '@securepeacock', SCYTHE '@scythe_io', Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an office application (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)  that initiate a network connection to a non-private IP addresses.
This rule aims to detect traffic similar to one seen exploited in CVE-2021-42292.
This rule will require an initial baseline and tuning that is specific to your organization.

value.title: PowerShell Initiated Network Connection
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a PowerShell process that initiates network connections. Check for suspicious target ports and target systems.

value.title: Use Short Name Path in Command Line
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali
value.description: Detect use of the Windows 8.3 short name. Which could be used as a method to avoid command-line detection

value.title: Use Short Name Path in Image
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali
value.description: Detect use of the Windows 8.3 short name. Which could be used as a method to avoid Image detection

value.title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects changing the PowerShell script execution policy to a potentially insecure level using the "-ExecutionPolicy" flag.

value.title: Read Contents From Stdin Via Cmd.EXE
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detect the use of "<" to read and potentially execute a file via cmd.exe

value.title: Wow6432Node CurrentVersion Autorun Keys Modification
value.author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
value.description: Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.

value.title: Suspicious Get-WmiObject
value.author: frack113
value.description: The infrastructure for management data and operations that enables local and remote management of Windows personal computers and servers

value.title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level - PowerShell
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects changing the PowerShell script execution policy to a potentially insecure level using the "Set-ExecutionPolicy" cmdlet.

value.title: Set Files as System Files Using Attrib.EXE
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the execution of "attrib" with the "+s" flag to mark files as system files

value.title: Modification of IE Registry Settings
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects modification of the registry settings used for Internet Explorer and other Windows components that use these settings. An attacker can abuse this registry key to add a domain to the trusted sites Zone or insert javascript for persistence

value.title: User with Privileges Logon
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects logon with "Special groups" and "Special Privileges" can be thought of as Administrator groups or privileges.

value.title: CurrentVersion Autorun Keys Modification
value.author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
value.description: Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.

value.title: Scheduled TaskCache Change by Uncommon Program
value.author: Syed Hasan (@syedhasan009)
value.description: Monitor the creation of a new key under 'TaskCache' when a new scheduled task is registered by a process that is not svchost.exe, which is suspicious

value.title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)
